ndent state-funded </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">schools</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. W</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e provide free advice and support to Free School applicant groups and have helped 70% of groups a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">pproved to open these schools</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0.1pt 0pt 0pt 14.2pt; text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">—</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Our suppo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rt is available to anyone but NSN’s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> focus is on </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">helping </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">teacher, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">school,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">parent</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, charity </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and community groups to develop a high quality application</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.2pt; text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">—</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We have restricted our responses to those elements</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> of the Inquiry</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> most relevant to Free Schools and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">raised some key questions that will need to be considered to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ensure that any </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">system</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> that approve</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and oversee</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> academies – including Free Schools – </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in future </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">do</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">es</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> not limit the potential of these new schools to improve standards.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 16.68pt; padding-left:1.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Improving student outcomes</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he first Free Schools </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">open</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> September </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2011</span><span style="font-family:Aria