 within the system</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">and the benefits of competition</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The opportunity to start a school from scratch has allowed teachers, charities, universities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, independent schools and community groups</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (oft</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">en in conjunction with parents)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">bring new ideas</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and expertise into the st</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ate sector, creating schools</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">which offer </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a new approach to meeting the needs of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">pupils in their area. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Amongst others, s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">chools have been set up by:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 35.7pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="color:#3fcfd5; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">—</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">41</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">parent/community </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">groups</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> often in areas where new school places are needed such as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Camden,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Runcorn</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Leeds</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 35.7pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="color:#3fcfd5; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">—</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">37</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> groups of t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">eachers,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> often in areas of high deprivation such as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Greenwich</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Knowsley and Sheffield; </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 35.7pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="color:#3fcfd5; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">—</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">27</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">harities </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and existing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">education </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">providers </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">including the Nation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">al Autistic Society,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Everton Football Club and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Southend YMCA</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 35.7pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="color:#3fcfd5; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">—</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">21</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> independent </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">schools, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">including Manchester Grammar School, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Brighton College</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and Eton College; and </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 35.7pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="color:#3fcfd5; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">—</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Four</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> universities – including King</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s Colleg</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e London and Exeter University.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Around 70%</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> of Free Schools have opened </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in areas where there is a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">need for new school places</span><a name="_ednref2"></a><a href="#_edn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, but they are also providing new good school places in areas where existing schools are underperforming.  Introducing choice for parents has been an important rationale for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">many groups, with 45% of pr</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">imary and 34% of secondary Free </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Schools opening in areas where the number of schools rated as ‘requires improvement’ or ‘inadequate’ is at or above the national average</span><a name="_ednref3"></a><a href="#_edn3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">New schools can</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> act as a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">catalytic </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">force, particularly </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">thanks to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the support they </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">receive</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> from local </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">parents. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The fact that parents, teachers, local businesses and other interested organisations can now dem</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and, and set up, a new school</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> – even where there is a surplus of places –</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> challenge</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s existing schools </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">reassess their own educational offer and attainment, helping to raise standards across the board. Anecdotally,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> we are already beginning to see the competitive impact of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Free Schools influencing the b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ehaviour of neighbouring schools</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">For example, since one primary Free School in Haringey started offering an extended day, a number of local primaries have </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">followed suit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. Similarly, since a Free School was approved to open on the Isle of Wight next year offering pupils Latin, several local</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> secondary schools have also decided to offer it.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:8pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:8pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Increas</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">ing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">innovation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">testing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> best practice </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Free</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Schools are leading</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> educational innovation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. Though all mainstream Free Schools </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">must offer their </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">pupils a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">broad and balanced curriculum, some of them take a different approach to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">teaching and learning</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. In many cases they </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">are</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">drawing on</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> international best practice and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">adopt</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">approaches from countries which consistently score highly in the PISA tests. Free Sch</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ools are now pioneering the use of:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 35.7pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="color:#3fcfd5; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">—</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">‘Core Knowledge’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> curricula, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">which </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a feature of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">many </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">top performing US states</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> used by Pimlico Primary Academy to raise the cultural liter</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">acy of deprived pupils</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">; </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 35.7pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="color:#3fcfd5; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">—</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">‘Forest School’ </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">education</span><a name="_ednref4"></a><a href="#_edn4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Aria