outstanding’ Free Schools, has recently </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">been approved to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">open</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> a second primary school</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> while </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Kha</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">lsa Primary School, a Sikh ethos Free School in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a deprived area of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Leeds</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> has been approved to open another school in Bradford </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">which will share its STEM focus. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Reaching</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> most disadvantaged </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2.12</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NSN</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> bel</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ieves that Free Schools should be targeting</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the most deprived </span><span styl